Summary: Large fireball looking round object moving southeast
divs: Sighting DetailsI was walking the dog and it was a very calm evening about 10:04 pm on May 29, 2012. While walking south on Arlington Avenue notice a large fireball looking round object moving southeast at appoximately 30 degrees. Took first picture with my cell camera and then looked at it and seemed to be more teardrop shaped. Then took a second picture and then looked at it and noticed that it was moving further away and there was actually a second similar object in the picture.
